        "min": 10,
        "max": 90,
        "value": 70,
        "unit": "%",
        "description": "Higher overlap ensures uniform coverage on irregular pine surfaces, preventing streaks; 70% balances efficiency and overlap-induced heating. Source: Process optimization studies in Optics Express (e.g., 2017 paper on scan strategies for laser cleaning, recommending 60-80% for woods)."
